Develop a PHP script to accept email addresses and validate it. Display the domain name of the
email and result of validation.

SOLUTION:
a PHP script that:
Accepts an email address (via form).
Validates the email format.
Extracts and displays the domain name of the email.

CODE:
<?php
$result = "";
$domain = "";

if ($_SERVER["REQUEST_METHOD"] == "POST") {
    $email = $_POST['email'];

    // Validate email
    if (filter_var($email, FILTER_VALIDATE_EMAIL)) {
        $result = "Valid Email Address ✅";
        
        // Extract domain name
        $parts = explode("@", $email);
        $domain = $parts[1];  // text after '@'
    } else {
        $result = "Invalid Email Address ❌";
    }
}
?>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Email Validation</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>Email Validation Form</h2>
    <form method="post" action="">
        <label>Enter Email:</label>
        <input type="text" name="email" required>
        <input type="submit" value="Validate">
    </form>

    <?php if (!empty($result)) { ?>
        <h3>Result: <?php echo $result; ?></h3>
        <?php if (!empty($domain)) { ?>
            <p><b>Domain:</b> <?php echo $domain; ?></p>
        <?php } ?>
    <?php } ?>
</body>
</html>

How It Works:
User enters an email (e.g., user@example.com).
filter_var($email, FILTER_VALIDATE_EMAIL) → Checks validity.
explode("@", $email) → Splits into username and domain.
For user@example.com → Domain = example.com.
Displays validation result and domain name.
